The paper deals with a problem of sequential decision making under uncertainty with both discrete and continuous variables, which is a common theme in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO). The problem involves planning and executing routes for an autonomous agent, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY). The paper also introduces a novel hierarchical planning framework, which could be of interest to researchers in machine learning (cs.LG) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA).
